Welcome back!  We hope you enjoyed your life changing study abroad experience in ${study_abroad_program}!   One of the next and final steps towards completing your study abroad program is reviewing and evaluating your study abroad experience.  Complete the Study Abroad Evaluation Form in your study abroad application portal. The evaluation only takes about 10-15 minutes and must be completed. This allows our office to know whether or not the program was effective and the future continuation of the program. We also hope to learn and grow from your responses, which allows us introduce future improvements to the office, programming, the application process, and more.  This is also a great way for you to tell us about your exciting adventures or if you found anything disconcerting about the programming.  Our office is here to listen and to provide you with support.  This evaluation is treated as confidential information. The context of the data is shared with Program Directors, but no names are revealed when we discuss the responses, unless it is otherwise specified in the evaluation.  So please feel free to be open and honest with your feedback.    We understand that upon returning from a program, one may experience Reverse Culture Shock, so all are welcome to come speak with our study abroad team if this is a concern for you or one of your peers.  Reverse Culture Shock can happen to anyone.  You can learn more about Reverse Culture Shock here.       Thank you for participating on our ${study_abroad_program} study abroad program!  We hope you had a wonderful experience and cannot wait to hear your feedback! Best regards, The Study Abroad Office

Greetings,
Thank you for registering for the online orientation for your Study Abroad ${study_abroad_program.u_term} program. Our office would like to remind you of the following information about orientation. Please also note that the online orientation will be made available to you a week after the live orientation.
"Students who miss the live orientation are more likely to experience concerns during their study abroad process. By missing the live presentation students are subject to miss vital information regarding the Study Abroad Office services, program payments, withdrawal process, tuition & fees, academic & student conduct, passports & visas, international students abroad (for international students), health abroad, safety abroad, what to expect abroad, travel tips, what to know before departure and upon your return. However, if students cannot make the orientation they will be provided a way to make-up the missed session and will be able to obtain the material covered.
It is the student's obligation to review the provided orientation material on their own, and obtain the necessary facts to be properly informed of the study abroad procedures. The Study Abroad Office will make sure the orientation material is sufficiently provided to students to complete within an adequate period, however the material may not be as in depth as it would have been during the live presentation. The live presentation allows time for questions and answers from attendees. After reviewing the material, students are welcome to seek clarification or inquire more about the process by reaching out to the Study Abroad Office.
The Study Abroad Office asks students to make every effort to attend the in-person session in order for the office to make sure students feel safe, secure, and aware of risks abroad, as well as provide students with the necessary knowledge regarding the study abroad procedures at Clayton State University.
Note that this absence does not excuse students from attending the Program Directors orientation. This is ONLY to excuse students from attending the Study Abroad Office's orientation."
Best Regards, The Study Abroad Office

Greetings from the Study Abroad Office!
Our team is excited to see you at the Study Abroad Orientation! We wanted to remind you of a few things in preparation for the event on Thursday, November 15, 2018.
Location: The orientation is located in the James M. Baker University Center in Room UC 322, located on the third floor of the UC building.
Time Frames: Orientation check-in begins at 6:15 PM, the check-in table will be outside of the classroom. The orientation will promptly begin at 6:30 PM. Please be on time so that we may try to end the orientation early.
Bring Refreshments: Bring a snack or light dinner! We know it's going to be a long day for you and appreciate you attending on a weekday! So please feel free to bring some refreshments to see you through the evening. We only ask that you bring something easy to eat (& to clean up) so that it does not distract the presenters or your peers.
What to Bring: Bring a writing utensil! We provide notepaper in the back of the 'Are You Prepared' handbook that you receive with your orientation packet. This way you may take notes or write down any questions you may have. Bring your laptop (if needed)! Do you have any questions or concerns about submitting your documentation? If so, please bring your laptop and/or mobile device and we will assist with any questions you may have about uploading your documentation.
We'll see you soon!
Best regards, The Study Abroad Office

Hello ${student_name}, Tuition and fees are due ${study_abroad_program.tuition_payment_deadline} for the Spring Study Abroad Program. Your current course registration for ${study_abroad_program.u_term} will reflect the fees associated with the study abroad program course that you will be taking while abroad. If you are taking other courses at Clayton State outside of the study abroad program, you will pay all associated tuition fees.  Refer to the information that was reviewed during the Study Abroad Orientation.  Please see below for more information about the tuition and fee process.     TUITION:  Tuition is separate from your study abroad program fees at Clayton State and payments must be made according to Clayton State's tuition deadlines.  Tuition must be paid before departure in order to obtain course credit for the program.  IMPORTANT: ${study_abroad_program.u_term} Tuition Payment Deadline is ${study_abroad_program.tuition_payment_deadline}. Refer to the reference links below:     Tuition Forms – the tuition fees form for undergraduate and graduate students.  If you are ONLY taking a study abroad course(s) over the summer, than you will only pay the following fees as mentioned on the form: In-State Tuition, the Technology Fee, the Card Fee, and the Institutional Fee.  Academic Calendar – student dates for tuition and fees can be located on the Academic Calendar by the associated term.  If you have completed or are in the process of completing this necessary step then we thank you for finalizing this step.  BURSAR For any other related questions regarding tuition and fees, you can contact the Bursar Office at 678-466-4295 or visit the Bursar website.  If you are in need of a payment plan for tuition, then check with the Bursar Office to verify if you are eligible for one.   STUDY ABROAD OFFICE Our office is here to assist with any questions or concerns you may have about the travel documentation.  You can visit us during our Semester Walk-In Hours or call/e-mail us for further assistance at StudyAbroad@clayton.edu or 678-466-4092. Thank you, The Study Abroad Office
